revision.text: ==English== ===Etymology=== {{confix|en|xylo|genous}} ===Adjective=== {{en-adj|-}} # {{lb|en|biology}} Living or growing on [[wood]]. #* '''1898''', ''Bulletin'' (issue 9, page 732) #*: Several of the '''xylogenous''' species appear to be of the same nature. The phyllogenous forms seem to be of a different character, but we are not concerned with them here. #* '''1901''', University of Nebraska, ''Contributions from the Botanical Survey of Nebraska'' #*: It occurs in nearly all maculicole fungi, and is exhibited by certain '''xylogenous''' fungi, such as Hysterographium.
